---
import { type Lang } from "@/i18n"

type Props = { lang: Lang }
const { lang } = Astro.props
---

<prose-content>
  {lang === "zh" ? (
    <>
      <h1>关于</h1>
      <p>「枢机」是一个人写的博客。</p>
      <p>
        这里只做一件事:在各个领域里,找那些数据已经悄悄转向、而共识还停在原地的地方,把判断写下来,留给时间检验。
      </p>
      <p>
        我不写四平八稳的综述。每一篇都会给一个明确、甚至可能让你不舒服的结论——但结论背后是数据和机制,不是情绪。有的判断以后会被证明是对的,有的会错;但每一篇都有数据留痕、有时间戳,认账。
      </p>
      <p>
        如果你也习惯对着主流叙事多问一句"数据真是这么说的吗",那我们大概聊得来。
      </p>
      <p>订阅 <a href="/zh/rss.xml">RSS</a>,或切换到 <a href="/about">English</a>。</p>
    </>
  ) : (
    <>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>The Seam is a blog written by one person.</p>
      <p>
        It does one thing: across different fields, it looks for the places
        where the data has already quietly turned while consensus is still
        standing where it was — and sets the judgment down, to be checked
        against time.
      </p>
      <p>
        I don't write tidy, hedge-everything surveys. Every piece lands a
        clear, sometimes uncomfortable conclusion — but the conclusion rests on
        data and mechanism, not mood. Some calls will prove right, some wrong;
        either way each one leaves a data trail and a timestamp, on the record.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you also tend to ask, of any mainstream story, "is that really what
        the data says?" — we'll probably get along.
      </p>
      <p>
        Subscribe via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>, or read in
        <a href="/zh/about"> 中文</a>.
      </p>
    </>
  )}
</prose-content>
